&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At SimplePractice, we are improving access to quality care by equipping health and wellness clinicians with all the tools they need to thrive in private practice.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;More than 250,000 providers trust SimplePractice to build their business through our industry-leading software with powerful tools that simplify every part of practice management. From admin work to clinical care, our suite of innovative solutions work together to reduce administrative burden—empowering solo and small group practitioners to thrive alongside their clients.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Award-winning and people-first, SimplePractice is shaping the future of health tech. Recognized by MedTech Breakthrough, the Digital Health Awards, and BuiltIn&#39;s Best Places to Work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;SimplePractice is looking for two Clinical Operations Leads to serve as embedded clinical voices at the intersection of technology and care — one focused on AI development and regulatory standards, and one on product development and clinical quality. Both roles sit within the Clinical Operations arm of our Clinical Division and are built for licensed mental health clinicians who believe that the best health technology is shaped by practitioners, not just built for them.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;Across both tracks, you will collaborate with cross-functional teams — product, engineering, data science, legal, marketing, and compliance — to ensure that what we build reflects the highest standards of clinical evidence, ethical integrity, and regulatory compliance. This is not a passive review function. You will be in the room shaping decisions, challenging assumptions, and holding us accountable to a standard that clinicians and patients deserve.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Sets Each Track Apart&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI &amp;amp; Regulatory Standards&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;This track is designed for a clinician who is energized by frontier technology and wants to help define what responsible clinical AI looks like. Day to day, you will:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;Review AI-generated clinical content, prompts, and features through a rigorous clinical and ethical lens&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;Contribute to internal frameworks governing how clinical AI is built, reviewed, and deployed&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;Partner with AI product and engineering teams to embed clinical standards throughout the development lifecycle&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;Bring cross-disciplinary knowledge of ethics, regulatory requirements, and payer standards to AI design decisions&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product &amp;amp; Clinical Quality&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;This track is designed for a clinician who wants to shape product decisions from the inside and champion the practitioner experience. Day to day, you will:&lt;/spa

